 :tx/rationale "PERF AUDIT FINDING P8-CONCEPT-SCANS: concept.rs contains 17 store.datoms() calls. Functions like concept_inventory, assign_to_concepts, co_occurrence_matrix, and compute_observe_steering_multi each do full O(N) scans. These run during every braid observe call. At 105K datoms with only 3 concepts and ~95 observations, scanning 105K datoms to find ~95 observation embeddings is wasteful. FIX: Use store.attribute_datoms() index lookups instead of full datoms() scans. The attribute_index already provides O(1) lookup by attribute — concept functions should use attribute_datoms(':concept/embedding'), attribute_datoms(':exploration/embedding'), etc. instead of filtering the full datom set. This is the same optimization applied to bilateral.rs in Session 032 (PERF-2). Verification: concept operations produce identical results. Performance: measure braid observe latency before/after. Traces to ADR-STORE-006. Depends on nothing."
